<p><strong>FL (Flawless):</strong> No inclusions or blemishes under 10x magnification — extremely rare. <strong>IF:</strong> No internal flaws, only minor surface marks. <strong>VVS1-VVS2:</strong> Very, very slight inclusions difficult even for trained gemologists to see at 10x. <strong>VS1-VS2:</strong> Small inclusions invisible to the naked eye — the industry "sweet spot." <strong>SI1-SI2:</strong> Easily seen at 10x; SI1 is usually eye-clean while SI2 can be borderline. <strong>I1-I3:</strong> Visible to the naked eye; may affect transparency and brilliance.</p>
<h3>The Eye-Clean Concept</h3>
<p>"Eye-clean" means no inclusions visible at about 25 cm with the unaided eye. VS2 and SI1 stones are typically eye-clean and offer the best value. FL and IF diamonds carry collector premiums but the visual difference is negligible without magnification.</p>
<h3>Clarity vs Price</h3>
<p>Each clarity step represents roughly 15-25% price difference. Unlike cut, the visual gap between VS2 and VVS1 is essentially zero without a loupe. Savvy buyers target VS1-VS2 and redirect savings toward cut or carat.</p>
<h3>Source Note</h3>
<p>Based on GIA clarity grading system, AGS standards, and Rapaport Diamond Report data.</p>`,
